## (Working Title) Metal

This is a world where metal resources have been used up. Precious metals are no non-existant and iron has taken their place. Rich and poor seperation is even further apart. Those that live outside the cities are farmers where city life can be harder. Jobs are hard to come by and little work is to be found. All benefits come from the government as well as all punishments.Plastics and polymers are the elements used in almost all clothing and other aspects. From tools to shoes, no metal can be found. If metal is needed then you'd have several guards watching it the entire time. Its not worth getting the government involved. 

The premise is based around a guy who takes care of his mother as farmer. His father passed away when the guy was young and the guy didn't really know his father. His mother stuggles to keep the magestrate away from interfering and taking her son away. Astin doesn't know why the magestrate would want him. He was just a poor soul farmer who provides the government with the grains and vegetables they ask for. He knows that he has one of the most efficient farms around even though he doesn't use any metals. That is why they try and keep a eye on him. The farm has around 12 employees. They often keep to themselves but are good people who do the work they need to do. The person he gets on with a lot is named Jethro but goes by the name Jet. He is an older man but knew the boys father. He tells him stories but never about what they did for work only that his dad was a smart and amazing person. Jet was also a very hard worker and often would tweak things on the farm to make them better. 

Astin did have a very calculating mind. One that would often look towards a certain way of doing things and looks at ways to refine it, to make it more efficient. He turned the acreage they "owned" and turned it into fields of bountiful edibles and foliage. He learned that certain seasons, only certain things would grow but also learned that every few cycles he had to let the land replenish its nutrients. He had requested the governemnt give them livestock so that he could fertilize the land and not have to wait a whole year or two before he could reuse a certain part of land but he is still waiting to hear back from them. its been 9 months with no word, and he didn't have his hopes up. 

He has often found ideas to make things better but required tools that were unavailbe to him. He often thought even something as simple as a stick with a sharp tool on the end in a curved fashion would help wonders cutting down the large grains and stalks. A long rock that he could flint could work but it would be very heavy and in the end might not work due to its unweildy weight. He had to settle with rock that he flinted only cutting a few grains at a time. An axe could work but again it was so large due the the rock that it wouldn't cut effeiently. 

The magestrate was a skinny weasel of a man. He had jet black hair and always used some type of glasses that were dark colored to cover his eyes. Astin always wondered and awed at what those were. Most strange that the magestrate often arrive on the farm on a thing he rode on. it had two wheels but not a wheel of wood but of some black material that made smoke come off them. Astin wasn't sure if it was the tires themselves or the speed that made the dirt rise up. 

## Synopsis
Countries rage war with one another via large robot battles for territory, though this fact is well hidden from the public. All metals are used use in conjunction to this purpose meaning all metals will be confiscated and punishment will ensue if they are hidden.

The main character's father was the creator and operator for the software that went into a battle system that allowed winners access to more resources and land. Constraints are put into place to keep countries within a certain limitation. The code created is currently in a read-only state where no new code can be implemented nor can the current code be changes. The main character's father was killed but only after his wife and his son moved outside the city and became ranchers under a psueonym. The father forgoe all ties to his previous life but left certain hints to his son in the form of his bed time stories. Often the stories would involve puzzle and riddles, as well as simple code phrases. Once the son is older and discovers his father was tied to the government he starts finding the clues that his father left behind for him to discover. This then takes him to a cave in the wilderness that requires him to sum up all the discovers his father left for him to unlock the door and access the facilty his father created in his time away from the government. In this cave is many computers and servers. He also left his some a special device that can tweak code in the form of an AI. 

Due to the lack of metal and electronic devices most people do not understand or know about technology. Since his father created the entire network infrastructure all devices emit a low frequency wave similar to wifi, the son can use this as a means to hack into them via the AI and view and tweak code. 

This doesn't trigger an alarm due to the AI's backend encryption and decryption code but it is soon found out that the backend code has been hacked and is being tweaked.

